oracle.spatial.rdf.client.jena

Class OraclePool

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.spatial.rdf.client.jena.OraclePool

  • public class OraclePool
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is a wrapper of OracleDataSource. It provides a pool of Oracle objects to facilitate application development.

    • Method Detail

      • close

        public void close()

      • getDefaultJdbcUrlPoolCacheProperties

        public static java.util.Properties getDefaultJdbcUrlPoolCacheProperties()
        Returns the default connection property values that can be used on a JDBC url pool object. Default values: MaxLimit="50" (maximum number of connections), InactivityTimeout="300" (seconds - physical connection can remain idle), ConnectionWaitTimeout="60" (seconds - time to wait available if all pool is used) ValidateConnection="true" (always validate a connection before getting from pool. Introduces about 50ms on each call, but connection should be automatically restored if database is restarted)
        Returns:
        the Properties java object
